Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1} until you have
¾ cup (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings). Drain @black beans{1} over a #small bowl{},
reserving liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}; cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}; cook until slightly darkened in color,
~{1%minute}.

Once onion is softened, add @organic ground beef{10%oz} to pot; season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}. Cook through the rest of the step as instructed.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Stir @mushroom stock concentrate{2} into pot. Add beans, half the
@crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz can}, 1 cup water, and ¼ cup reserved bean liquid into
pot. (For 4 servings, use all the crushed tomatoes, 2 cups water, and ½ cup bean
liquid.) Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened,
~{5-8%minutes}.

> Prefer your broth a bit thicker? Simmer a little longer—or simmer a little
> less if you prefer a thinner broth! You're the chef, after all.

Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Crush a few @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz}.

Divide soup between bowls and top with @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup},
@smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp}, and as many crushed tortilla chips as you like.
(Tip: Start with a few crushed chips and add more as you go to keep them crunchy!)
Serve with whole tortilla chips on the side.